Tiffany constantly lies to you, in anyway possible -- 'she will give you a discount' -- (which ends up being a lie) -- 'she will refund your money' (which ends up being a lie).  Now, the store's solution / (offer) is to give me store credit for food.  I will not take that option.  I refuse to take that option.  Tiffany, the store manager -- has now alienated -- one of this store's best known customers.  I will no longer (ever) do business with this store.  If I do not get my money back via 'a dispute' with my bank.  I will definitely take this store to small claims court.  Enough is enough.  Tiffany, the store manager -- has clearly tried to ripped-me-off.  I have given this store too many chances -- over, & over again.  Regarding, this store (itself),....  This store often takes forever -- to usually deliver your food (hours, upon hours). Plus, I have received numerous pizza pies -- that the pizza has arrived 'rail thin'; & no I did not order the thin pizza option.  In addition, this store gives you very little toppings.  Often, this Papa John's pizza store at 529 Stanley Avenue, Brooklyn, New York 11207 does not bake your pizza fully (often arrives undercooked) -- in my opinion.  Also, this store is known to give you very little sauce on your pizza.  Enough is enough,......  I can no longer take the very poor service anymore -- after all these years of ordering.  Tiffany, the store manager -- trying to rip-me-off with a telephone order (that she told me -- I must make with her (over the telephone) -- to get the 35 percent off discount from her) -- was my 'last straw' from this store.  The order ended-up being $302.52.  After making the order with her over the telephone, & hanging-up.  I noticed (right away) that she did not give the 35 percent-off that she offered to me previously (from the store messing-up my previous Papa John's app. pizza order).  So, I called her back (fairly quickly), & she promised (paraphrasing) -- 'to cancel my order, & refund my all money' -- which clearly ended-up being a lie.  Once again, I am done with this Papa John's franchise pizza store at 529 Stanley Avenue, Brooklyn, New York 11207.  I will now fight with all my might -- for my money back.  I do not like to be lied to; nor, do I like to be ripped-off.  I will not forget.  I never forget -- when I am screwed-over.  Get up, Stand up!'  'Get up, Stand up.  Stand up for your rights.' -- Bob Marley
